STRINGS: ...My futile struggle has finally reached its end.
In a few moments, I'll be chopped up and die
to satisfy her dark desires.
She must've grown proficient from the murders she stacked up.
She must also be familiar with methods to kill and prolong suffering.
She might scrape off my skin while not touching my internal organs,
only to then remove my limbs and disembowel me, leaving just
my respiratory and circulatory systems intact.
In the meanwhile, my eyes, ears, brain, and sense of pain
will cruelly remain active as all my essential organs are
taken from me one by one.
Frankly, I've lost hope.
Still, I don't know any way to escape from this hell.
I've given up, my body refusing to even tremble.
"I don't care anymore...
Just finish me already."
"...Alright. But since you worked so hard for me,
I'll make this special--"
"I shall kill you, Blindman style.
I'll reach as deep into your eyes as possible...
following through until I arrive at the brain."
"...A stickler to the end, huh."
"Yes. After all, this is a good opportunity."
"Opportunity... for what?"
"Ah, welcome back!"
She cheerfully left the room and sprinted towards the entrance.
"Such perfect timing, I'm so thankful...!
I was just about to do it now."
"Please, come in, come in.
I'll show you to the best spot in the house!"
Lumbering footsteps slowly approached the room I was in.
My eyes went wide at the sight of the person
she had escorted inside.
"Hey there... Houjou.
How are you holding up?"
"...Soujirou Sekimoto...!!"
I was supposed to have resigned myself to my fate,
yet rage like boiling magma welled up from the pit of my stomach.
"How much does Houjou know?"
"Everything, Professor.
I even told her about the letters I sent you
while you were in jail."
"Perhaps you are under some kind of misapprehension.
That biting look on your face worries me, you know."
"Were you just using me!?"
"Maybe, maybe not.
But that doesn't matter at this juncture, does it?"
"What a great expression, Ms. Houjou.
I knew learning this very last twist
would certainly shake you up."
"Now this makes your murder worth my while. Ufufu."
"Sekimoto Soujirou... the police WILL track you down."
"Listen. Humans invariably die someday.
In my previous case, my life was in the government's hands.
That sort of threat doesn't work anymore."
"Besides, this state of affairs
stimulates my academic curiosity to the utmost limits."
"Sanae Makimura is a very interesting specimen.
She granted flesh to my armchair theory."
"Professor Sekimoto...!"
She gazed at Soujirou Sekimoto, spellbound.
"If I am given a chance, I'd love to study your deeds in detail
and publish a paper on you from behind bars."
Sanae Makimura had tears in her eyes.
Is this the 'I want to be needed by someone' thing she spoke of?
In this situation that perverts common sense,
I seem to be going nuts myself.
"How lucky I am to learn the happenings of
this C Town amidst my trial.
And then to be able to witness their conclusion so near at hand."
I don't want to end up the victim of these two psychos' desires--
At this rate, my being will only serve as fodder for their pleasure.
I can't possibly bear being helplessly taken apart alive
just to gratify their sadistic passions.
"Now, Makimura. Do show me
how Blindman operates."
"Certainly...!"
She again gripped a large pair of scissors.
Drawing near one or two steps, her expression was that of delight.
"Even if you rob me of my vision, I'll never forget your faces.
If there is a world after death, I won't stop until you writhe and boil
in the cauldrons of hell."
"Shut up... Right now, I'm standing on the grandest stage.
I'd rather your vulgar chattering not interrupt me."
Sanae Makimura seized my jaw with great strength.
And forced my head to turn upwards.
In the edge of my field of vision, I saw her face,
seemingly having arrived at the heights of pleasure.
Soujirou Sekimoto, pouring his frigid gaze on her back.
The ceiling, stained with violent blood sprays.
That was everything in my view.
And what may very well be the last things I'll ever see in my life.
She unhurriedly brought the massive scissors right in front of my eyes.
Meticuously sharpened just for this day,
the inner side of the opened blades keenly shined silver.
"Now then, die for me.
I'm truly grateful--"
"Gah...agh...gh...!"
"Agah...wh...
Why...do...this...to me...!?"
Makimura, suddenly stabbed through the chest by Soujirou Sekimoto,
was pinned down by him as she collapsed unto the floor.
Her countenance told of her disbelief.
She reached her hand as to try to remove the weapon
sticking out of her back, but he brutally trampled it underfoot.
The vivid noise of splitting tree bark--
Sekimoto had crushed her fingers without hesitation.
"Pro...professor...?
Professor...!"
Since he had mercilessly aimed at the heart,
her body was losing drastic amounts of blood.
Regardless, her body thrashed about in an attempt to save itself.
Clatteringly.
Unproductively.
From the puddle of blood formed due to this exercise in pointlessness
emanated splashing noises of heavy viscosity.
"Does it hurt, Sanae Makimura?"
"He...help...me..."
"Do you want this to end right away, Sanae Makimura?"
His quiet question
didn't seem to reach her ears.
"However, I'm sorry to say that this is me
showing you as much mercy as I can.
You weren't this lenient with your victims, were you?"
"Won't you die alone in this filthy room,
polluted by murderous intentions and grotesqueries,
miserably and horribly for me, Sanae Makimura?"
"That is the least you could do
to those you murdered."
Tear streamed from her eyes as if to beseech him.
In response to that,
he slowly brought his lips close to her ear.
"Now then... Makimura."
"Show me--"
"Blindman's final moments.
You are needed for that."
He pulled the blade stuck in her heart out
and pitilessly jabbed it into her carotid artery.
Fresh blood spouted like a water fountain from her back and neck,
but it settled down shortly afterwards,
and Sanae Makimura stopped moving, completely.
Her final expression was somewhat enraptured.
"Haa... haa... phew..."
"It's over... Are you well, Houjou?"
He inquired before planting himself down, exhausted.
"I've lived the detention center lifestyle for too long,
and haven't done sufficient exercise,
so that took me out..."
I looked at him, unable to hide my surprise.
"You... what were you after from the outset?"
"...What I genuinely hoped to achieve was..."
"...to take responsibility."
"Responsibility...?"
In that word, I felt an uncharacteristic sense of remorse.
Sekimoto calmly muttered, a weight behind his tone.
"Even the murder I committed was an accidental killing
while I tried to subdue a student inspired by Blindman."
"This town's tragedy was the same.
The trifling spirit of academic inquiry my mind bore
engendered the sacrifice of so many people."
"That is why I decided to devote my life
to taking accountability."
"Enough casualties have been made...
But with this, I might be able to take responsibility
for all my mistakes."
